You look so much like your mum in some of this Vlog! (That's a good thing....your mum is gorge!) I totally understand what you mean about having days when you just feel a bit bad about yourself. What has helped me is to really examine the sexism of the beauty industry - remembering that the stereotype of beauty is so narrow for a reason, less than 1% people look the way models do, which is the point...the businesses work by making us feel bad about ourselves so we have to buy their product to 'fix' our flaws, that's how they make money. I think about whether my friends fit into the beauty stereotype, and they don't, but I still think they're beautiful...so I extend that kindness to myself. It makes me angry so I deliberately try not to fit into the beauty stereotype - I rarely wear make up, don't shave, etc. - as an act of rebellion!
